Popular producer and Mavin Records honcho, Don Jazzy, joined other entertainers such as Timini Egbuson and Seyi Awolowo for the ‘watch party’ the movie, ‘Dwindle’. Directed by the duo of Kayode Kasum and Dare Olaitan, and produced by Mimi Bartels, the film tells the story of a group of people— Nedu, Buta, Tolani and Juliet— who over the course of some days, had a series of unfortunate events befall them. Chinedu is a down-on-his-luck hustler who lost his job on the first day because of a government ban on commercial motorcycles in the state, while Buta is a street urchin that had been squatting with Sogo, a happy-go-lucky guy with ‘street credibility’. On the other hand, female police officers, Tolani and Juliet, are are charged with an assignment to protect the Governor of Dakawa State. Unfortunately he is kidnapped on their watch and they are accused of the crime. Fans of popular actress, Funke Akindele, would see a different side of her in the movie as she played the role of a zealous police officer alongside Bisola Aiyeola. Other actors in the movie include Jidekene Achufusi (Swanky JKA), Gregory Ojefua, Broda Shaggi, Adedimeji Lateef, Taymesan, Uzor Arukwe, Timini Egbuson, Efa Iwara and Steve Chuks. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com